modules.description: Provides scatter-gather I/O operations for sending and receiving data through sockets, along with the ability to transmit file descriptors as ancillary data. Works with byte sequences, socket file descriptors, and ancillary data structures. Used for efficient network communication in systems requiring low-level control over data transmission and file descriptor passing.

Sends and receives data over Unix sockets, supporting ancillary file descriptor passing. It handles raw byte buffers and arrays for efficient data transfer. Used for inter-process communication where file descriptors need to be transmitted alongside message data.
